Sentencas: The stability of the anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell consisting of Ni-YSZ vertical bar YSZ vertical bar LSM was examined at 800 degrees C: by monitoring the current density at a constant terminal voltage of 0.5 V.
Titulo: Sudden Deterioration in Performance During Discharge of Anode-supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Although stable power generation was possible within initial 60 min, gradual decrease and subsequent sudden drop in current density were observed: a series of this behavior was different from that observed in limiting current density.
Titulo: Sudden Deterioration in Performance During Discharge of Anode-supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: This behavior is suggested to be one of the degradation factors related with transport of gas species in the pores of the electrode.
Titulo: Sudden Deterioration in Performance During Discharge of Anode-supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In response to performance deterioration, a drastic increase in ohmic loss and impedance was confirmed soon after the discharge operation.
Titulo: Sudden Deterioration in Performance During Discharge of Anode-supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: It is noted, however, that the deteriorated performance was reversibly recovered depending on the holding time under the open-circuit condition.
Titulo: Sudden Deterioration in Performance During Discharge of Anode-supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Analogous phenomena occurred with the cell consisted of Ni-YSZ vertical bar YSZ vertical bar Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 vertical bar La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3, indicating that the cause of the sudden deterioration was in the anode side.
Titulo: Sudden Deterioration in Performance During Discharge of Anode-supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
